<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="String1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">String,</orth> subst. any thin line or cord: <emph>I'll knit it</emph> (the hair) <cit><quote>up in silken --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.7.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 7, 45</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>spiders' --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.289" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 289</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>good --s to your beards,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 4.2.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. IV, 2, 36</bibl></cit> (to tie them fast). <cit><quote>hast had my purse as if the --s were thine,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 1.1.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 1, 3</bibl></cit>.<lb />== fibre, nerve, tendon (cf. <emph>Heart-string</emph>): <bibl n="shak. jn 5.7.55" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 7, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.105" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 2, 105</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.3.70" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 3, 70</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.216" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 3, 216</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.11.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 11, 57</bibl>.
<lb />== the cord of a musical instrument: <bibl n="shak. son 8.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 8, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.2.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 2, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.5.46" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 5, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.6" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.1.57" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 1, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.364" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 364</bibl> <cit><quote>(harp not on that s.).</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.109" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 109</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.4.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 4, 46</bibl> <cit><quote>(silken --s).</quote> <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.292" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 3, 292</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.1.81" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 1, 81</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>